					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex, Sephardi semi-cursive script, unpunctuated.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">194 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>190/185</height>
										<width>150 </width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>115 </height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>194 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>27 quires: i4+1 (1-5), ii8+1 (6-14), iii-xv8 (15-118), xvi8-1 (119-125), xvii-xxvi8 (126-189), xxvii8-4+1 (190-193+194). </p>
									<p>Catchword on every verso.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several mutilated folios.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="30" writtenLines="30">Watermarks on <locus n="2r"/>, and on <locus n="fse001r"/>. The first watermark is a hand, the second watermark is a vase with a crescent at the top and a monogramm (CO?), similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">3603</ref> (dated to 1646, England).<p>Pricking and hard-point ruling are visible. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable. </p>
									<p>Folio 194r-194v is a later reconstruction. </p>
									<p>Deleted and rewritten section on folio 25v. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Sephardi semi-cursive script, unpunctuated.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus n="19r"/> and <locus n="25v"/>- contain two erased passages, which have been restored by a later hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>ʾAvraham ʾibn ʿEzraʾ ha-Sefaradi (author): inscribed with his name in the author’s colophon (40v). </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>  	Post-1600. Ivory parchment binding, tooled in black.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
